Equity analysis on educational attainment by ethnicity groups in the Bay Area

1 Educational attainment by race

Educational attainment shows disparity among difference race population. White alone enjoys a generally higher level of education whereas other races have a generally lower level. Educational levels are polarized within Asian groups.

2 Educational attainment by ethnicity groups, focusing on latinx

The educational level disparity between white (not Latinx) and Latinx is severe, while the other remaining ethnicity groups appear homogeneous.

3 Latinx group educational attainment overrepresentation in year 2006 to 2019 in the Bay Area

The educational attainment level of the Latinx group in the Bay Area is significantly over-represented by the total population. Below shows how much Latinx population (25 years old and above) with no college degree is over-represented by the total populatin in the specified county. Among nine counties in the Bay Area, the educational attainment issue appears most pressing in Marin County. ALl nine counties are over-represented.
